00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:41,000
[Strange Tales of Tang Dynasty II: To the West]

3
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:44,030
[Episode 16]

4
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:56,539
Lu Lingfeng,

5
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,030
don't panic!

6
00:01:58,430 --> 00:02:00,150
Brother has made arrangements in advance.

7
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,880
The bandits have been subdued.

8
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:05,900
Mr. Su,

9
00:02:06,150 --> 00:02:07,710
your strategic planning is impressive.

10
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:08,910
I, Jiang, admire you.

11
00:02:09,460 --> 00:02:10,320
It's nothing.

12
00:02:10,669 --> 00:02:11,150
Come on.

13
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,800
Let's hurry and think of a way

14
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,310
to open this door.

15
00:02:18,990 --> 00:02:19,590
Let me.

16
00:02:32,579 --> 00:02:33,240
Step aside.

17
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:07,790
You actually made it here alive?

18
00:03:08,950 --> 00:03:10,880
How exactly should we address you?

19
00:03:11,750 --> 00:03:12,580
Landlady,

20
00:03:12,990 --> 00:03:13,910
Mrs. Mo,

21
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:16,350
or treasure hunter?

22
00:03:18,510 --> 00:03:19,750
For a dying person,

23
00:03:20,070 --> 00:03:21,790
whatever you call me will just be your last words.

24
00:03:21,790 --> 00:03:22,520
I don't mind.

25
00:03:22,829 --> 00:03:23,550
Lady,

26
00:03:24,030 --> 00:03:25,960
you lost the game of Tokhara knife.

27
00:03:26,070 --> 00:03:27,070
You must accept the consequences.

28
00:03:27,070 --> 00:03:29,829
When will we have our wedding night?

29
00:03:34,880 --> 00:03:36,150
Who do you think you are

30
00:03:36,670 --> 00:03:38,150
to take advantage of me?

31
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:43,390
Hermit,

32
00:03:44,510 --> 00:03:46,040
why did you align with them?

33
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:48,530
Someone was killed in the remote inn,

34
00:03:48,710 --> 00:03:50,700
turning it into a place of disputes.

35
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:51,829
As someone outside the secular world,

36
00:03:51,829 --> 00:03:53,030
why didn't you leave?

37
00:03:53,150 --> 00:03:55,750
The one standing in front of you is not a hermit,

38
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:57,600
but the sheriff of this county.

39
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:01,000
You're an official?

40
00:04:01,910 --> 00:04:03,180
And a sheriff, no less?

41
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:06,560
I was so stupid.

42
00:04:08,230 --> 00:04:09,960
I actually spared these people

43
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:11,840
just because of you.

44
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:12,730
So what?

45
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:13,990
Should we thank you

46
00:04:13,990 --> 00:04:15,230
for sparing us?

47
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,050
You were staying at my inn,

48
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:19,050
drinking my wine, eating my food.

49
00:04:19,320 --> 00:04:21,850
If I wanted to kill you, would it be difficult?

50
00:04:22,910 --> 00:04:23,990
You, little girl,

51
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:26,550
seem to have some experience in Jianghu.

52
00:04:26,550 --> 00:04:28,070
You tested the water and the wine

53
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:29,190
with Yong'an Pills.

54
00:04:29,190 --> 00:04:29,990
Wait a minute.

55
00:04:30,010 --> 00:04:31,160
But if I were to

56
00:04:31,190 --> 00:04:32,510
poison your food,

57
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:34,310
could you tell?

58
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:39,190
You're quite capable.

59
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:41,380
You even know

60
00:04:41,420 --> 00:04:42,590
we used Yong'an Pills.

61
00:04:42,590 --> 00:04:44,670
In those two superior rooms you were staying in,

62
00:04:44,670 --> 00:04:45,990
just one night's sleep

63
00:04:46,540 --> 00:04:47,909
would make you blind

64
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:49,950
by the next morning.

65
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:51,850
No matter how great your martial arts skills are,

66
00:04:51,850 --> 00:04:54,310
what difficulty would I have in killing you?

67
00:04:56,950 --> 00:04:57,909
Moro incense

68
00:04:58,470 --> 00:05:01,390
can blind people just by smelling it for one night.

69
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:03,710
You're quite vicious!

70
00:05:04,100 --> 00:05:04,950
In that case,

71
00:05:04,980 --> 00:05:06,300
I should thank you for arranging for me

72
00:05:06,300 --> 00:05:07,700
to sleep in the woodshed?

73
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,920
I could have

74
00:05:10,510 --> 00:05:11,710
easily killed them.

75
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:13,790
It was all because of you.

76
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:14,950
When you arrived,

77
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:16,610
I couldn't bear to see you die.

78
00:05:17,030 --> 00:05:19,030
So I used the Tokhara knife instead,

79
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,910
trying to scare everyone away.

80
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:22,720
Let me tell you,

81
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:23,690
Sheriff Jiang,

82
00:05:24,270 --> 00:05:25,390
the moment you entered the in,

83
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:27,590
the way she looked at you was different.

84
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:29,270
She has taken a liking to you.

85
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:30,990
If you weren't a sheriff,

86
00:05:30,990 --> 00:05:32,830
she'd probably want to marry you

87
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:35,110
and make you the landlord of her Mo's Inn.

88
00:05:37,420 --> 00:05:38,740
Say something.

89
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:42,830
Your voice is also pleasant to hear,

90
00:05:43,690 --> 00:05:45,420
like that of a celestial being.

91
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:52,110
Boy-crazy!

92
00:05:53,430 --> 00:05:54,110
You...

93
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:57,150
really are a sheriff?

94
00:06:00,230 --> 00:06:00,950
Indeed.

95
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:06,670
As Jiang Wei, the sheriff of Shen County,

96
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:08,070
I'm now questioning you.

97
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,670
Where are the 34 construction workers

98
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:12,610
of Shen County now?

99
00:06:13,870 --> 00:06:15,190
It seems you truly are.

100
00:06:17,030 --> 00:06:17,890
How old are you?

101
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:18,670
Answer me!

102
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,300
Where are the construction workers?

103
00:06:22,590 --> 00:06:23,630
Are they safe?

104
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:33,159
Are you 23 years old?

105
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:37,490
If my younger brother were still alive

106
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:38,950
this year

107
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,159
he would be this age.

108
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:44,290
When he was little, I asked him

109
00:06:44,350 --> 00:06:46,550
what he most wanted to be when he grew up.

110
00:06:47,230 --> 00:06:47,909
He said

111
00:06:48,460 --> 00:06:50,060
he most wanted to be a sheriff

112
00:06:50,990 --> 00:06:54,470
because the official who catches thieves is the most impressive.

113
00:06:54,470 --> 00:06:57,870
You built an inn in the wilderness above

114
00:06:58,230 --> 00:07:00,910
because you discovered the Vajra Temple

115
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:03,630
buried underground.

116
00:07:04,550 --> 00:07:05,870
Your aim

117
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,970
is Master Moshi's tongue relic, right?

118
00:07:10,710 --> 00:07:12,370
You are truly knowledgeable.

119
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:14,430
Once again, you've got it right.

120
00:07:14,430 --> 00:07:15,490
Treasure hunters,

121
00:07:15,860 --> 00:07:18,190
seeking treasures for those who pay them.

122
00:07:18,270 --> 00:07:20,730
It's just that this time, it took some effort

123
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:22,480
and was delayed for half a year.

124
00:07:22,790 --> 00:07:24,430
You treasure hunters

125
00:07:24,790 --> 00:07:27,150
are no different from thieves.

126
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:29,350
Even if your brother were still alive,

127
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:31,070
he would be implicated by you,

128
00:07:31,110 --> 00:07:32,790
unable to take the imperial examinations,

129
00:07:32,790 --> 00:07:35,050
and even less likely to become a sheriff.

130
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:36,470
Do you think we want to be

131
00:07:36,470 --> 00:07:37,530
treasure hunters?

132
00:07:38,630 --> 00:07:39,470
Back in the day

133
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:42,030
my dad was a mobile corps commander,

134
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,690
but he was wrongfully framed,

135
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:46,390
and our entire family was to be executed.

136
00:07:46,390 --> 00:07:47,990
If we hadn't escaped in time,

137
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,870
my dad and I

138
00:07:49,909 --> 00:07:51,310
would have died long ago.

139
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:53,070
It's just a pity that

140
00:07:54,430 --> 00:07:55,470
my brother...

141
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:58,900
Those despicable officials...

142
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,310
He was only 11 years old, and they actually...

143
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:18,290
Since the late years of Empress Wu Zetian,

144
00:08:18,520 --> 00:08:20,180
the court has been in turmoil,

145
00:08:20,180 --> 00:08:21,980
and informing has been rampant.

146
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:24,310
Even the frontier army

147
00:08:24,350 --> 00:08:26,080
couldn't avoid the influence.

148
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:27,790
I can tell that

149
00:08:28,350 --> 00:08:29,830
you probably

150
00:08:29,870 --> 00:08:31,400
all are veterans.

151
00:08:32,270 --> 00:08:32,870
Now,

152
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,549
a new emperor has ascended the throne

153
00:08:35,590 --> 00:08:36,830
and granted amnesty to the whole country.

154
00:08:36,830 --> 00:08:39,789
Why don't you try to appeal for justice

155
00:08:39,950 --> 00:08:42,230
and clear your names?

156
00:08:45,980 --> 00:08:47,070
It's too late.

157
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:49,410
We've killed too many people.

158
00:08:49,830 --> 00:08:51,430
We can't clear our names now!

159
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:53,110
Who cares about the name?

160
00:08:53,390 --> 00:08:54,790
Following the Treasure Hunting Grandmaster,

161
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:56,270
the gold and silver we've accumulated

162
00:08:56,270 --> 00:08:58,070
have been piling up like mountains.

163
00:08:58,070 --> 00:08:59,340
Which one of you officials

164
00:08:59,340 --> 00:09:01,470
dares to say you're richer than us?

165
00:09:04,550 --> 00:09:05,160
Everyone,

166
00:09:06,630 --> 00:09:08,590
it was all because that sheriff pretending to be a hermit

167
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:09,790
looks like my brother

168
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:11,630
that I didn't kill them all

169
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:12,470
up there.

170
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:14,760
Now I have to trouble you all

171
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:16,270
to take action together.

172
00:09:20,820 --> 00:09:22,500
I am Lu Lingfeng,

173
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:24,910
the former general of the Imperial Guards.

174
00:09:24,910 --> 00:09:26,040
All you old brothers

175
00:09:26,110 --> 00:09:27,470
once served in the army.

176
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:29,670
Anyone who hasn't committed murder

177
00:09:29,670 --> 00:09:31,310
can surrender their weapons.

178
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:33,440
I will do my best to ensure your safety.

179
00:09:37,230 --> 00:09:39,140
I am Su Wuming, a disciple of Detective Di.

180
00:09:39,140 --> 00:09:40,740
I am willing to vouch for you.

181
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:55,350
Lu, Su,

182
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:56,950
since you are so eager to die,

183
00:09:56,950 --> 00:09:58,210
I will grant your wish!

184
00:10:14,590 --> 00:10:15,320
Lu Lingfeng,

185
00:10:15,550 --> 00:10:16,870
don't kill those who surrender.

186
00:10:16,870 --> 00:10:17,950
Make this quick!

187
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:29,210
Leave this woman to me!

188
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:33,970
Found it, found it!

189
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:35,150
I finally found it!

190
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,380
I finally found it!

191
00:11:55,830 --> 00:11:56,430
Daughter?

192
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,440
Brothers?

193
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,880
Grandmaster, help!

194
00:12:01,270 --> 00:12:01,890
Grandmaster,

195
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,790
save us!

196
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:04,110
Daughter,

197
00:12:04,590 --> 00:12:05,550
are you alright?

198
00:12:05,910 --> 00:12:06,480
I'm fine!

199
00:12:06,870 --> 00:12:08,100
I told you long ago

200
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,150
not to be kind.

201
00:12:08,470 --> 00:12:10,960
[Treasure Hunting Grandmaster]

202
00:12:09,620 --> 00:12:11,110
Why can't you remember?

203
00:12:12,710 --> 00:12:15,070
I even gave you winter clothes to keep warm.

204
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:16,730
How could you say such things?

205
00:12:18,670 --> 00:12:19,430
sir,

206
00:12:19,830 --> 00:12:21,430
how about I give you a piece of clothing?

207
00:12:21,430 --> 00:12:22,230
Bring it here.

208
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:24,710
Your words and actions

209
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:27,750
have desecrated the sacred place where Master Moshi

210
00:12:27,890 --> 00:12:29,710
translated scriptures, debated,

211
00:12:29,710 --> 00:12:32,230
and turned a robber into a Buddha.

212
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:35,500
Moshi?

213
00:12:39,630 --> 00:12:41,690
That old monk was indeed remarkable.

214
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:44,030
His tongue turned into a relic.

215
00:12:46,230 --> 00:12:48,070
Do you know how much the employer paid

216
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:49,550
for this small piece?

217
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,680
You were once a mobile corps commander.

218
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:55,780
How could you let profit drive you

219
00:12:55,780 --> 00:12:57,030
to do such a thing?

220
00:12:57,270 --> 00:12:58,730
What does it matter to you?

221
00:13:00,260 --> 00:13:02,230
The Sogdian businessman in the ancestral hall

222
00:13:02,230 --> 00:13:03,630
was killed by you, right?

223
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:05,530
I wanted to eat chestnuts.

224
00:13:06,150 --> 00:13:07,880
So I went to the town to buy some.

225
00:13:07,950 --> 00:13:09,830
When I returned,

226
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:12,030
I saw a red ribbon tied to the gate

227
00:13:12,390 --> 00:13:14,520
and knew that many people had moved in.

228
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:17,540
I could only enter via the rooftops.

229
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:36,970
Let me ask you this:

230
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,590
Where are the construction workers from Shen County

231
00:13:41,590 --> 00:13:42,790
who built the inn now?

232
00:13:43,790 --> 00:13:45,320
The construction workers?

233
00:13:49,310 --> 00:13:51,190
They built the inn for me.

234
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:54,270
I chose a nice place with mountains and water

235
00:13:54,270 --> 00:13:57,350
for them to rest in peace.

236
00:13:57,580 --> 00:13:58,130
We

237
00:13:58,510 --> 00:13:59,550
owe each other nothing.

238
00:13:59,550 --> 00:14:00,780
You killed them?

239
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:03,710
That was 34 lives!

240
00:14:04,010 --> 00:14:06,280
Compared to the ruins of the Vajra Temple

241
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:09,030
that I painstakingly searched for,

242
00:14:09,710 --> 00:14:10,950
a few lives

243
00:14:12,350 --> 00:14:13,150
mean nothing.

244
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:14,440
You old villain!

245
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:15,790
You killed too many people

246
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,340
and committed heinous sins.

247
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:17,960
Brothers,

248
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:19,790
let's capture him together!

249
00:14:19,790 --> 00:14:20,270
Okay!

250
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:37,440
Boss, run!

251
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,040
Brothers!

252
00:14:49,570 --> 00:14:50,110
Step back!

253
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:50,910
Xijun, hurry!

254
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:36,990
Fed.

255
00:15:38,230 --> 00:15:39,690
Do you recognize this beast?

256
00:15:39,690 --> 00:15:41,340
I was about to ask you the same question.

257
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:42,830
Aren't you the knowledgeable one?

258
00:15:42,830 --> 00:15:45,060
You read those supernatural notes all day long.

259
00:15:45,060 --> 00:15:46,590
What the heck is this thing?

260
00:15:47,590 --> 00:15:49,520
I've never seen this thing either!

261
00:15:51,150 --> 00:15:52,710
This is underground.

262
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:54,460
Could it be...

263
00:15:54,780 --> 00:15:55,710
Could it be what?

264
00:15:56,350 --> 00:15:58,640
Could it be the legendary Fushu?

265
00:15:59,890 --> 00:16:02,150
There are three fierce beasts underground:

266
00:16:02,150 --> 00:16:04,240
Wangxiang, Boqi,

267
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:05,260
and Fushu.

268
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:06,200
This Fushu,

269
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:07,810
looks like a pig but isn't quite a pig,

270
00:16:07,810 --> 00:16:09,110
and like a sheep but isn't quite a sheep.

271
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,170
It loves to eat the brains of the dead.

272
00:16:16,070 --> 00:16:17,870
Is there a special way to subdue this beast?

273
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:18,950
If it takes any longer,

274
00:16:18,950 --> 00:16:20,470
I'm afraid it will be too late.

275
00:16:20,470 --> 00:16:21,380
Chicken Fed!

276
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:23,890
Why are you looking at me?

277
00:16:23,890 --> 00:16:25,150
I don't have any ideas.

278
00:16:25,190 --> 00:16:26,880
I don't have any pepper with me right now.

279
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:27,430
and besides,

280
00:16:27,430 --> 00:16:29,230
even if I did, it might not work.

281
00:16:32,710 --> 00:16:34,350
Underground beast?

282
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:38,870
Brother, what are you thinking?

283
00:16:39,950 --> 00:16:40,670
Cypress!

284
00:16:41,470 --> 00:16:42,310
Cypress?

285
00:16:42,590 --> 00:16:43,450
Think about it.

286
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:45,230
Why do people choose

287
00:16:45,470 --> 00:16:47,190
burial sites with cypress trees

288
00:16:47,190 --> 00:16:48,820
when burying the dead?

289
00:16:49,310 --> 00:16:51,310
